attaches it, and makes the call. In the second phase, it only runs if the server returns `Unauthenticated`, which means the token was valid by the client's clock but the server rejected it anyway, typically because it expired in the window between fetch and transit. At that point, `ForceRefresh` is called instead of `GetValidAccessToken`: unlike the optimistic fetch, `ForceRefresh` bypasses the cache entirely and goes straight to the auth service, guaranteeing a fresh token. Both phases attach the token identically — `authorization` metadata, same `Bearer` format, just a different token value — so the interceptor defines a local helper at the top of the closure to avoid repeating that call. If `ForceRefresh` fails, the session is unrecoverable and the error is returned directly to the caller without further retry.

```go
// Unary gRPC client interceptor: optimistic call with cached token, one refresh-and-retry on Unauthenticated
func authInterceptor(tokenSource TokenSource) grpc.UnaryClientInterceptor {
    return func(ctx context.Context, method string, req, reply interface{},
        cc *grpc.ClientConn, invoker grpc.UnaryInvoker, opts ...grpc.CallOption) error {

        attach := func(ctx context.Context, t string) context.Context {
            return metadata.NewOutgoingContext(ctx, metadata.Pairs("authorization", "Bearer "+t))
        }
        token, err := tokenSource.GetValidAccessToken(ctx)
        if err != nil {
            return err
        }
        if err = invoker(attach(ctx, token), method, req, reply, cc, opts...); status.Code(err) != codes.Unauthenticated {
            return err
        }
        token, err = tokenSource.ForceRefresh(ctx)
        if err != nil {
            return err
        }
        return invoker(attach(ctx, token), method, req, reply, cc, opts...)
    }
}
```

Register the interceptor when creating your gRPC connection:

```go
// Creates a gRPC client connection with the auth interceptor registered
conn, err := grpc.Dial(
    userServiceAddress,
    grpc.WithTransportCredentials(credentials.NewClientTLSFromCert(nil, "")),
    grpc.WithUnaryInterceptor(authInterceptor(myTokenSource)),
)
```
